DESIGN INTENT
-------------
Purinina deliberately runs inside a hardened Docker sandbox and ships a
consistent Human-In-The-Loop (HITL) policy: dangerous actions require explicit
human approval before execution. These controls are safety features, not
guarantees. Do not disable them unless you fully understand the consequences.

NETWORK MODEL
-------------
For pentesting to work, the sandbox shares the host network stack
(`--network host`) and is granted raw-socket capabilities. This is powerful and
intentional. It means the container can reach everything the host can reach.
Run Purinina only from a machine and network position from which you are
authorized to operate.

